{"word":"ἐρρωμένος","slug":"ἐρρωμένος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐρρωμένος</b></el> <el>(ἐρρωμένος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> of <a href='S:ρώννυμι'><el>ρώννυμι</el></a>, used as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>\n<p/><i>in good health, stout, vigorous</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>ἄρρωστος</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <a href='S:irregular'>irreg.</a> <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a>, <el>ἐρρωμενέστερος</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: —<a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>-έστατος</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἐρρωμένως</el>, <i>stoutly, manfully, vigorously</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/>"}]}